==Coaches==

=== Coaching changes ===
In 2019 the ACC Conference will have 4 new head coaches for the 2019 season.

* On November 11, 2018, Louisville head coach [[Bobby Petrino]] was fired after starting the season 2–8.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/25242973/bobby-petrino-fired-louisville-cardinals-coach|title=Bobby Petrino fired as Louisville coach|website=espn.com|first=Mark|last=Schlabach|date=November 11, 2018|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref>  The interim coach, [[Lorenzo Ward]], was not retained and [[Scott Satterfield]] was announced as the new head coach on December 2, 2018.<ref>{{cite web |title=Scott Satterfield era at Louisville brings a needed infusion of belief |url=https://www.courier-journal.com/story/sports/college/louisville/2018/12/04/louisville-football-scott-satterfield-takes-reins/2200762002/ |website=The Courier-Journal |language=en}}</ref>
* On November 25, 2018, North Carolina head coach [[Larry Fedora]] was fired<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/25373518/north-carolina-fires-coach-larry-fedora|title=Larry Fedora fired by North Carolina after 7 seasons|website=espn.com|publisher=ESPN|date=November 25, 2018|access-date=February 28, 2019}}</ref> and replaced by returning coach [[Mack Brown]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.sbnation.com/college-football/2018/11/26/18104882/mack-brown-unc-coach|title=UNC's really, officially bringing back Mack Brown|work=[[SB Nation]]|first=Alex|last=Kirshner|access-date=December 26, 2018}}</ref>
* On November 28, 2018, Georgia Tech head coach [[Paul Johnson (American football coach, born 1957)|Paul Johnson]] announced his retirement from coaching effective after Georgia Tech's bowl game.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ramblinwreck.com/johnson-steps-down-as-head-coach/|title=Johnson Steps Down As Head Coach|website=RamblinWrech.com|access-date=November 28, 2018}}</ref> On December 7 it was announced [[Temple Owls football|Temple]] head coach [[Geoff Collins (American football)|Geoff Collins]], a former grad assistant and recruiting coordinator for Georgia Tech, would be the new head coach.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ramblinwreck.com/collins-named-georgia-tech-football-head-coach/|title=Collins Named Georgia Tech Football Head Coach|date=2018-12-07|website=Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets|language=en-US|access-date=2018-12-07}}</ref>
* On December 30, 2018, Miami Hurricanes head coach [[Mark Richt]] announced his retirement from coaching and was replaced by [[Manny Diaz (American football)|Manny Diaz]]. Diaz was previously the defensive coordinator at Miami and had been hired on December 13, 2018, to be the head coach at Temple.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.si.com/college-football/2018/12/30/manny-diaz-new-head-coach-miami-mark-richt|title=Miami Names Manny Diaz Head Coach After Mark Richt Steps Down|website=www.si.com|access-date=January 4, 2019}}</ref>

